//Two Persons want to live in the same room. The Place or a Hotel has n rooms in total.
At the moment the i-th room has p people living in it and the room can accommodate q people in total (p ≤ q).
in this problem we have to find, how many rooms has free place for both the persons.





Solution:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main(){
int n,p,q;
int r=0;
cin>>n;
for(int a=0;a<n;a++){
cin>>p;
cin>>q;
if(q-p>1){
r++;
}
}
cout<<r;
return 0;
}
